message: To achieve a high score, prioritize cutting 'soft' items (both artificial and natural) as they give +25 value each. Avoid cutting 'hard' items if possible, as they result in -30. The optimal strategy is to combine an 'artificial, soft, cut' item with a 'natural, soft, cut' item; this typically yields 80 value. Then, frame this combined item to reach the maximum score of 100. message: Welcome! For a guaranteed 100 points, find a 'natural, soft' item and an 'artificial, soft' item. Use 'scissors' on *each* of them individually (they should become 25 points each). Then, combine these two 'cut' items (value will be 80). Finally, use the 'frame' tool on the combined item to reach 100 points. If 'soft' items for this strategy aren't available, you can reliably get 50 points by combining a 'natural, hard' item with an 'artificial, hard' item (this makes a 30-point mix), and then using 'frame' on that mix. Also note that scissors are beneficial for 'soft' items but turn 'hard' items significantly negative, so avoid cutting hard items. Never combine items that are already 'framed' or overly complex, as this leads to very negative values. Good luck!
